stimulus:
Welcome to Interactive Stroop Test with Stimulus Onset Asynchrony.

Press any key to begin.

You will see text randomly in one of the four colors, Blue Red Green Yellow.

Your task to to press a key designated to the color stimulus as soon as possible.

Here is a list of the colors with associated keys.

  • Blue - key B
  • Red - key R
  • Green - key G
  • Yellow - key Y

For example, you should press B when seeing a stimulus of color Blue, even if it is presented with another word like Red.

Here is a tip, you can place your figures on the keys to have a better performance.

For instance, left middle figure on R; left index figure on B; right index figure on G; and right middle figure on Y

The experiment will start with a practice for you to become familiar with the task.

Then a test will start.

Press any key to begin the practice.

The test will start. Remember to press the key according to the color rather than the word.

Press any key to begin.
